# games / bevy

Bevy is a free, open-source, data-driven game engine built in Rust around an Entity Component System (ECS). Game code, scenes, and the render pipeline are all authored as plain Rust/Cargo source — there is no separate scripting language. For OOTA the canonical headless deliverable is a single rendered PNG frame, produced via Bevy's official `headless_renderer` pattern: a camera renders to a GPU image, a render-graph node copies it to a CPU buffer, and the main world saves a PNG with `WinitPlugin` disabled and `ScheduleRunnerPlugin` driving frames — no window or display server. On macOS this runs on the Metal/wgpu backend with no extra system deps.

